        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When calling:\nZend_Controller_Action_Helper_Redirector::setGotoRoute(array(\"action\" => \"fooBar\"));\n\nThe url's camelCase isn't handled. It ends up:\nhttp:\/\/localhost\/controller\/fooBar\n\nIt should end up:\nhttp:\/\/localhost\/controller\/foo-bar\n\nI've solved this in a quick and dirty way:\nif (isset($urlOptions[\"action\"])){\n  $urlOptions[\"action\"] = strtolower(ereg_replace(\"[A-Z]\", \"-&#92;&#92;0\", $urlOptions[\"action\"]));\n}\n\nThe real fix should probably be in Zend_Controller_Router_Route::assemble()"
        },
